{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/4407.American_Gods", "title": "American Gods", "titleComplete": "American Gods (American Gods, #1)", "description": "Days before his release from prison, Shadow's wife, Laura, dies in a mysterious car crash. Numbly, he makes his way back home. On the plane, he encounters the enigmatic Mr Wednesday, who claims to be a refugee from a distant war, a former god and the king of America. Together they embark on a profoundly strange journey across the heart of the USA, whilst all around them a storm of preternatural and epic proportions threatens to break.Scary, gripping and deeply unsettling, American Gods takes a long, hard look into the soul of America. You'll be surprised by what - and who - it finds there...This is the author's preferred text, never before published in the UK, and is about 12,000 words longer than the previous UK edition.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1258417001i/4407.jpg", "genres": ["Mythology", "Fiction", "Urban Fantasy", "Audiobook", "Fantasy", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "Horror", "Adult", "Contemporary", "Science Fiction"], "publisher": "Headline Review", "series": ["American Gods"], "author": ["Neil Gaiman"], "publishDate": 1109923200000, "characters": ["Odin (Norse mythology)", "Hinzelmann", "Mr. Jacquel", "Mr. Wednesday", "Mr. Ibis", "Mr. Nancy", "Mr. World", "Samantha Black Crow", "Shadow Moon", "Mr. Town", "Easter", "Chad Mulligan", "Spider", "Whiskey Jack", "Technical Boy", "Media", "Margaret Black Crow", "Laura Moon", "Bilquis", "Mad Sweeney", "Loki", "Czernobog"], "places": ["Illinois", "The United States of America", "Wisconsin", "Chattanooga, Tennessee", "Chicago, Illinois", "Minnesota"], "ratingHistogram": [18524, 45592, 151225, 319509, 399586], "ratingsCount": 934436, "reviewsCount": 47350, "numPages": 635, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Bram Stoker Award", "awardedAt": 978336000000, "category": "Best Novel"