{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/491093.The_Healer_s_War", "title": "The Healer's War", "titleComplete": "The Healer's War", "description": "A novel of the Vietnam War, with a magical, mystical twist.Lt. Kitty McCulley, a young and inexperienced nurse tossed into a stressful and chaotic situation, is having a difficult time reconciling her duty to help and heal with the indifference and overt racism of some of her colleagues and with the horrendously damaged soldiers and Vietnamese civilians whom she encounters during her service at the China Beach medical facilities.She is unexpectedly helped by the mysterious and inexplicable properties of an amulet, given to her by one of her patients, an elderly, dying Vietnamese holy man, which allows her to see other people's \"auras\" and to understand more about them as a result. This eventually leads to a strange, almost surrealistic journey through the jungle, accompanied by a one-legged boy and a battle-seasoned but crazed soldier and, by the end of the journey, McCulley has found herself and a way to live and survive through the madness and destruction.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1286829764i/491093.jpg", "genres": ["Fiction", "Speculative Fiction", "Urban Fantasy", "Historical", "Historical Fiction", "Fantasy", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "War", "Science Fiction", "Historical Fantasy"], "asin": "0553282522", "isbn": "0553282522", "isbn13": "9780553282528", "publisher": "Bantam Spectra", "author": ["Elizabeth Ann Scarborough"], "publishDate": 620636400000, "ratingHistogram": [66, 130, 520, 646, 431], "ratingsCount": 1793, "reviewsCount": 155, "numPages": 312, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Nebula Award", "awardedAt": 599644800000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/598099.The_Quantum_Rose", "title": "The Quantum Rose", "titleComplete": "The Quantum Rose (Saga of the Skolian Empire, #6)", "description": "A New Adventure in the Saga of the Skolian Empire.Kamoj Argali is the young ruler of an impoverished province on a backward planet. To keep her people from starving, she has agreed to marry Jax Ironbridge, the boorish and brutal ruler of a prosperous province. But before Argali and Ironbridge are wed, a mysterious stranger from a distant planet sweeps in and forces Kamoj into marriage, throwing her world into utter chaos.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1391409221i/598099.jpg", "genres": ["Fiction", "Futuristic", "Space", "Science Fiction Romance", "Audiobook", "Fantasy", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "Space Opera", "Romance", "Science Fiction"], "asin": "0812568834", "isbn": "0812568834", "isbn13": "9780812568837", "publisher": "Tor Science Fiction", "series": ["Saga of the Skolian Empire"], "author": ["Julie Bell", "Catherine Asaro"], "publishDate": 1014019200000, "characters": ["Havyrl Valdoria", "Kamoj"], "ratingHistogram": [76, 227, 639, 706, 407], "ratingsCount": 2055, "reviewsCount": 150, "numPages": 432, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Nebula Award", "awardedAt": 978336000000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}]}
