{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/68020.Powers", "title": "Powers", "titleComplete": "Powers (Annals of the Western Shore, #3)", "description": "Young Gav can remember the page of a book after seeing it once, and, inexplicably, he sometimes \"remembers\" things that are going to happen in the future. As a loyal slave, he must keep these powers secret, but when a terrible tragedy occurs, Gav, blinded by grief, flees the only world he has ever known. In what becomes a treacherous journey for freedom, Gav's greatest test of all is facing his powers so that he can come to understand himself and finally find a true home.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1440562098i/68020.jpg", "genres": ["Young Adult", "Magic", "Fiction", "Speculative Fiction", "Teen", "Audiobook", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "Fantasy", "High Fantasy", "Science Fiction"], "asin": "0152057706", "isbn": "0152057706", "isbn13": "9780152057701", "publisher": "Clarion Books", "series": ["Annals of the Western Shore"], "author": ["Ursula K. Le Guin"], "publishDate": 1188630000000, "ratingHistogram": [42, 194, 1009, 1937, 1841], "ratingsCount": 5023, "reviewsCount": 467, "numPages": 502, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Nebula Award", "awardedAt": 1199174400000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Locus Award", "awardedAt": 1199174400000, "category": "Best Young Adult Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Endeavour Award", "awardedAt": 1199174400000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/352777.Seeker", "title": "Seeker", "titleComplete": "Seeker (Alex Benedict, #3)", "description": "The Barnes &amp; Noble ReviewAlex Benedict and his executive assistant, Chase Kolpath -- ambitious antiquities dealers from Jack McDevitt's A Talent for War (1989) and, more recently, Polaris -- are back in Seeker, a story in which the two antiquarians search for a legendary lost colony that is both a science fiction thriller and a remarkably complex mystery.More than 9,000 years after an interstellar transport named Seeker left an overcrowded and politically repressive Earth with the dream of founding a new society on an unspecified planet, Benedict and Kolpath stumble across a ceramic cup that was once on the now-legendary lost starship. But tracking down how the ancient artifact got from the ship into the hands of a maltreated woman and her thuggish boyfriend turns out to be more than Benedict and Kolpath bargained for -- as their search leads them across multiple star systems and straight into an anonymous assassin's crosshairs. But as the killer closes in, the two courageous antiquarians uncover the jaw-dropping truth about the lost starship and the legendary colony Equally reminiscent of Frederik Pohl's Hugo and Nebula Award-winning Heechee saga (Gateway, Beyond the Blue Event Horizon, et al.) and a classic Ellery Queen mystery, McDevitt's Seeker will appeal to readers of hard-core science fiction, as well as adventurous mystery fans looking for an out-of-this-world story. And just like Polaris, Seeker is characterized by a bombshell of an ending that will leave readers absolutely awestruck. Paul Goat Allen", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388302002i/352777.jpg", "genres": ["Adventure", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Speculative Fiction", "Space", "Audiobook", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "Space Opera", "Aliens", "Science Fiction"], "asin": "0441013759", "isbn":